post_text: Good Morning CESD Parents. This is the basic outline of the school day schedule. Your respective school sites and teachers will be sending out more detailed information in the coming week. The 100% digital platform is a new challenge for us all. Please understand in advance that there are many moving part to making the 100% digital delivery a success. There will be times when the internet doesn't work, there will be times when a student gets disconnected from their Zoom Room, and there will be times when everything works great. Your patience in this school partnership is truly appreciated during these challenging times. We need to remember, this is a first time for all of us.

Chowchilla Elementary Families have been requesting information regarding the upcoming on-boarding process for the start of school, as well as a general idea of what the instructional bell schedule will look like to start the year. Stay tuned for a call from your child's teacher. The class lists will also be posted Monday, August 10th after 4pm on the district website. You will also be able to find that information in your Aeries Parent Portal on Monday after 4 pm.

The district is in the process of updating its ability to rapidly share information with families. This process will be accomplished in your Aeries parent portal. So please, be sure that you complete the re-enrollment process (even if nothing has changed). Having updated cell phone, email, and mailing address information is vital. Stay Safe!

post_text:
The Chowchilla Elementary School District will be providing online-only instruction to start the school year. Until the current surge in Madera County flattens (less than 100 positive cases per 100,000 residents) and rapid testing (on a large scale) becomes readily available, the ability to safely start up our schools is not achievable. The District will be providing information via traditional mail, district website, Facebook, auto-dialer, etc...Stay Tuned!

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact your child's school site (August 4th-Offices Open) or the District Office at 559-665-8000. These are unprecedented times and our staff is working hard to provide strategies and resources in support of the on-line instructional platform. Starting our schools in an online platform is not our first choice. However, at this time, it is the most common sense and safest choice!

The safety of our students, staff, families, and community members will continue to be the primary guidepost for our decisions.

post_text:
The Chowchilla Elementary School District will be opening school on a traditional calendar starting August 18, 2020. In order to open, and stay open, the District will need the support of all families as safety precautions will be implemented. Additionally, we appreciate those families that indicated they could transport their child to school rather than use the bus. This will allow us to minimize the number of students riding the buses each day. At this time, it is our belief that the best place for our children is at school.

Families electing to have their children participate in the 100%-Online-Virtual Academy can do so by going to the Virtual Academy Registration link on the District Website: https://www.chowchillaelem.k12.ca.us/Page/770

Although the initial plans are to start the school year on a traditional schedule. However, we should always be prepared to pivot should a state or county mandate require school closures.

post_text: Congratulations to current Fuller Elementary Principal Michelle Worrell for being selected as the new Assistant Superintendent of Educational Services for the Chowchilla Elementary School District. She will be replacing Linda Russell-Scheet who will be retiring in January. Pictured is Michelle being recognized as the 2017 Madera County Administrator of the Year. Michelle has worked in many capacities (teacher, coach, vice principal, and principal) for the District. She will bring to her new position a high level of enthusiasm and expertise.
text: Congratulations to current Fuller Elementary Principal Michelle Worrell for being selected as the new Assistant Superintendent of Educational Services for the Chowchilla Elementary School District. She will be replacing Linda Russell-Scheet who will be retiring in January. Pictured is Michelle being recognized as the 2017 Madera County Administrator of the Year. Michelle has worked in many capacities (teacher, coach, vice principal, and principal) for the District. She will bring to her new position a high level of enthusiasm and expertise.

post_text: Welcome to Fuller Elementary Mr. Blair Lambert! In July, Blair will be taking over the duties as Principal of Fuller Elementary. Pictured with Blair is his mother Karolyn Lambert, a former Fuller Elementary student and Chowchilla High School Redskin. Blair comes to us from the Clovis Unified School District. In 2005, Blair began his teaching career at Harold Woods Elementary. During his time at Harold Woods Blair taught first, second, fourth, and sixth grade. Most recently, Blair is the Learning Director at Clovis West High School. Blair will bring to the District a high level of enthusiasm, many relevant experiences, and a passion to support the children and families of our community. The District is excited to have Blair become a member of our Educational Family. Congratulations Blair!

post_text: Chowchilla Elementary School District FAMILIES - Next Tuesday, May 5th, the District will be distributing the 3rd Round of student work packets. The pick-up time for the packets will be from 9:00am - 1:00pm. Stephens school will distribute at their own school this time around. On the same day, school sites will also be "collecting" work packets 1 and 2. Please bound or bag (like in a paper grocery bag) the student work. Then put your student and teachers name on the outside. The site will collect the done work as you pick up the new work. The work will be routed to the teacher(s). The District truly understands the many challenges families are facing with the Shelter in Place order. Your patience and support in helping your children get their work completed while keeping everybody safe is very much appreciated.

The safety of all students, families and loved ones in our community is, and will continue to be our priority.

The Chowchilla Elementary School District will be closed effective March 16th and tentatively until April 13th.
A re-evaluation of the re-opening date will take place when more information is available.

As Fresno and Madera Counties function in many ways as a shared population, the Madera County Health Officer, Department of Public Health, and the Superintendents of Madera County public school districts have come to consensus that it is best to close public schools in
Madera County. School closure is effective immediately.

As information becomes available the District will be posting it on their website, sharing information via Facebook, and sending out information on the auto-dialer.

post_text:
Art Exhibition: Chowchilla: The Place We Call Home‚Äù

Chowchilla City Hall presents an art exhibition reflecting a personal and emotional view of Chowchilla through the art of the students of Wilson Middle School. On display will be 20 ‚Äì 25 graphite drawings, watercolors, and acrylic paintings of images from the beloved city. The opening reception will be held on Wednesday, February 26th from 4:00 p.m. ‚Äì 5:30 p.m. at Chowchilla City Hall (with a special performance by Wilson Middle School Music Department.) Refreshments will be provided. The art exhibition is curated with the cooperation of City of Chowchilla Director of Recreation and Community Engagement Marty Piepenbrok, Wilson Middle School Vice Principal Alicia Jackson, and Wilson Middle School Art Instructor Karen Stojanovski, with the help and support of Wilson Middle School and Chowchilla City Hall. Artwork will be on display through March 15.
